posts.description:
Today I knocked off another buck list objective that has been on my list for years, climb Mt. Hood, the highest point in Oregon. Not only that but I got to do it with style, climbing up the Reid Headwall (a much more technical route then the standard) and skiing back down the mountain. 
The most beautiful part of climbing Mt Hood was getting to see the bizarre rim ice cliffs and in the case of the Reid Headwall we climbing through a maze of rim ice cliffs and towers (pictured). So beautiful. I've never seen anything like it in real life. Hood truly is a stunningly beautiful mountain and deserves its place as one of "The 7 Wonders of Oregon".
